## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 901](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section901&num=0&edition=prelim) lets you credit foreign tax against your U.S. tax; [26 U.S.C. § 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) caps that credit. The "allowed" credit per basket is `min(available foreign tax, [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) limit)`. Excess available foreign tax that can't be used this year rolls forward under [§ 904(c)](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim). This stage computes the baseline credit before any treaty re-sourcing add-on (which is layered on at US25-15 to US25-19).

{% set base = rule.outputs[0].value | from_json -%}
For 2025:

- Available general-basket foreign tax (US25-13): **{{ base.general_available_foreign_tax_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Available passive-basket foreign tax: **{{ base.passive_available_foreign_tax_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**

Applying `min(available, [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) limit)` per basket:

- **Allowed general-basket FTC:** **{{ base.allowed_general_ftc_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- **Allowed passive-basket FTC:** **{{ base.allowed_passive_ftc_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- **Total baseline allowed FTC** (sum across baskets): **{{ base.total_allowed_ftc_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**

After applying baseline FTC to regular tax, **remaining U.S. tax = {{ base.regular_tax_after_ftc_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**, and the remaining nonrefundable cap from [Form 1116](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1116) line 33 is **{{ base.remaining_form_1116_line_33_cap_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**. Both numbers feed the treaty re-sourcing worksheet at US25-15 onward.

